## Top 5 This Week

1. **Entra Backup and Recovery is GA** — Critical identity objects (users, groups, apps, Conditional Access policies, and more) are now automatically backed up daily and restorable. If you hold Entra ID P1 or P2, this is live in your tenant now. Review recovery procedures before you need them.

2. **Passkeys become the default authentication method in Entra ID** — Microsoft has shifted the default sign-in experience to passkeys and overhauled the SMS/voice authentication model. If you haven't started a passkey rollout, you're now behind the platform default. Plan your communication and Conditional Access updates accordingly.

3. **Advanced Intune Suite capabilities now included in M365 E3/E5** — The December 2025 licensing restructure took effect July 1. Endpoint Privilege Management, cloud PKI, and other Suite features are now part of E5 with select capabilities in E3. Audit your current add-on spend and update your provisioning baselines.

4. **Cross-Tenant Message Recall in Exchange Online is GA** — Recall now works across organizational boundaries, not just within your tenant. If you manage inter-org mail flow or have data handling policies around misdirected email, validate whether this capability changes your incident response runbook.

5. **GPT-5.6 live in Microsoft 365 Copilot** — OpenAI's GPT-5.6 is available today in Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Chat, and Cowork. Stronger multi-step reasoning means agentic Copilot tasks perform meaningfully better. No admin action required, but expect users to notice the quality delta and ask questions.

