## Identity & Access

- **[Microsoft Entra Backup and Recovery is now generally available](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-backup-and-recovery-is-now-generally-available/ba-p/4521997)** [GA] — Rolling out to all workforce tenants this week for Entra ID P1/P2 licensed customers, this capability automatically backs up core directory objects daily, including users, groups, apps, service principals, managed identities, Conditional Access policies, named locations, and authentication methods. Document your recovery runbook now and assign ownership to who can initiate a restore. This directly addresses accidental bulk-delete and ransomware-driven identity tampering scenarios.

- **[Microsoft Entra ID security updates: Passkeys are the default authentication method in Entra ID](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/)** [GA] — Passkeys are now the platform default sign-in experience in Entra ID, and the SMS/voice authentication model has been restructured. Read the full post to understand the new SMS gating model before users start hitting friction. Update your Conditional Access policies and end-user guidance to align with this shift.

- **[Bring business logic into PIM role activation workflows](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/bring-business-logic-into-pim-role-activation-workflows/ba-p/4531380)** [Preview] — Custom extensions for Entra PIM are now in preview, letting you gate role activation on external context such as ticket validity, HR status, compliance posture, or on-call schedules via Logic Apps or custom APIs. For environments where PIM approvals are currently manual and context-blind, this closes a real governance gap. Start with your highest-privilege roles and design extension logic before broad rollout.

- **[Defending SaaS-based applications against ShinyHunters OAuth abuse](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/defending-saas-based-applications-against-shinyhunters-oauth-abuse/)** [GA] — Microsoft Threat Intelligence has tied ShinyHunters activity to vishing, supply-chain compromise, and misconfigured guest access targeting SaaS OAuth flows. Review your app consent policies, audit OAuth grants for third-party apps in your tenant, and verify guest access restrictions are configured intentionally. This is active threat actor tradecraft, not a theoretical risk.

- **[Windows 365 for Agents: A secured execution environment for AI agents](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/windows-365-for-agents-a-secured-execution-environment-for-ai/ba-p/4529336)** [GA] — Windows 365 now offers dedicated Cloud PCs purpose-built for running enterprise AI agents, with consistent identity, policy enforcement, and visibility baked in. For security teams struggling to govern agents running on shared or unmanaged infrastructure, this provides a managed execution plane. Evaluate this against your current agent deployment architecture if you're moving agents to production.

---

## Endpoint & Device Management

- **[Advanced Microsoft Intune capabilities now available in Microsoft 365 E3 and E5](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/advanced-microsoft-intune-capabilities-now-available-in/ba-p/4529335)** [GA] — Effective July 1, the December 2025 packaging changes are live: advanced Intune Suite capabilities including Endpoint Privilege Management, cloud-based PKI, and AI-assisted operations are now included in M365 E5, with select capabilities in M365 E3. If your organization was paying for Intune Suite as a standalone add-on, audit whether those licenses are now redundant. Update procurement and provisioning documentation to reflect the new entitlement model.

- **[Understanding Windows monthly updates: Servicing explained](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/understanding-windows-monthly-updates-servicing-explained/ba-p/4532290)** [Preview] — Microsoft published an updated guide on Windows monthly servicing, distinguishing mandatory security updates from optional non-security preview releases. Useful as a reference for onboarding new admins or re-aligning stakeholders who conflate preview updates with production-required patches. Share with your patch management team to standardize terminology and update cadence decisions.

- **[Windows news you can use: June 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/windows-news-you-can-use-june-2026/ba-p/4532288)** [GA] — Windows 11 version 26H2 is available for testing via the Windows Insider Program, sharing the same servicing branch as 25H2 and 24H2, meaning deployment uses an enablement package with minimal user disruption. Windows 365 also received Build 2026 updates including ready-to-code Cloud PCs and expanded AI agent support. Enroll test devices in Insider channels now if you need lead time before 26H2 reaches broad availability.

