## Collaboration & Productivity

- **[Cross-Tenant Message Recall in Exchange Online](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/cross-tenant-message-recall-in-exchange-online/ba-p/4535800)** [GA] — Message Recall now works across tenant boundaries, one of the most-requested Exchange Online enhancements since cloud-based recall launched in April 2023. If your organization handles sensitive inter-org mail and has existing data loss incident response procedures around misdirected messages, update those procedures to account for this new recall capability. No admin enablement is documented as required, but verify behavior in your environment.

- **[Available today: OpenAI's GPT-5.6 in Microsoft 365 Copilot](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/available-today-openai-s-gpt-5-6-in-microsoft-365-copilot/ba-p/4533152)** [GA] — GPT-5.6 is the new preferred model for M365 Copilot, available now in Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Chat, and Cowork, with stronger reasoning for agentic and multi-step tasks. No admin action is required to enable it, but expect users to notice performance improvements and increased reliance on Copilot for complex workflows. Update adoption materials to reflect the improved capability baseline.

- **[SharePoint Showcase: How Microsoft uses Copilot in SharePoint, and how you can get started](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-sharepoint-blog/sharepoint-showcase-how-microsoft-uses-copilot-in-sharepoint-and/ba-p/4533156)** [GA] — Microsoft published real internal use cases for Copilot in SharePoint alongside a recap of all recently GA'd SharePoint platform functionality. The companion post on building AI skills is worth reviewing if you're standing up Copilot agents grounded in SharePoint content. Use this as a reference for justifying and scoping SharePoint Copilot deployments with stakeholders.

---

## AI & Copilot

- **[Dataverse Is Your Agent Data Platform: Here's What's New in July 2026](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/power-platform/blog/2026/07/06/dataverse-july2026/)** [GA] — July Dataverse updates include expanded coding agent marketplace coverage, broader MCP tool connectivity, certified partner MCPs for trusted adoption, and enterprise governance controls for internal MCPs. If you're building or governing Power Platform agents, the MCP governance additions are the most operationally significant. Review the certified partner MCP list and establish an approval process before users start connecting uncertified MCPs.

- **[Native Dataverse Authorization (Public Preview) for Stronger Security in Power Pages](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/power-platform/blog/power-pages/native-dataverse-authorization-public-preview-for-stronger-security-in-power-pages/)** [Preview] — Authorization for external users in Power Pages is now enforced directly within Dataverse rather than at the portal layer, providing stronger security and improved visibility without changing the maker experience. For environments exposing Dataverse data to external users via Power Pages, this is a meaningful security architecture improvement. Evaluate the public preview in a non-production environment and plan migration from legacy authorization as the feature approaches GA.

