## Security & Compliance

- **[CVE-2026-63801: tipc — fix slab-use-after-free Read in tipc_aead_decrypt_done](https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/vulnerability/CVE-2026-63801)** [GA] — MSRC published this Linux kernel TIPC subsystem vulnerability this week. Review applicability if your environment includes Linux workloads managed through Defender for Endpoint or Azure-hosted Linux VMs. Apply vendor patches as they become available and monitor MSRC for severity ratings.

- **[CVE-2026-60082: DBI versions before 1.651 for Perl do not enforce statement handle consistency](https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/vulnerability/CVE-2026-60082)** [GA] — Affects Perl DBI library versions prior to 1.651. Relevant if your organization runs Perl-based automation or scripts in managed or monitored environments. Inventory Perl DBI usage and update to 1.651 or later.

- **[CVE batch: drm/amdkfd, drm/amdgpu, drm/amd/display, netfilter ebtables, KVM SEV, ALSA asihpi](https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/vulnerability/CVE-2026-63882)** [GA] — MSRC published six additional Linux kernel CVEs this week covering AMD GPU drivers, netfilter, KVM SEV, and ALSA audio. These affect Linux kernel components and are relevant for Linux endpoints, Azure VMs, and environments where AMD GPU passthrough is in use. Track these through your Linux patch pipeline and apply fixes as distributions package them.

- **[Protecting Microsoft at AI speed: How SFI proactively hardens our cloud](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/08/protecting-microsoft-at-ai-speed-how-sfi-proactively-hardens-our-cloud/)** [GA] — Microsoft published a detailed post on how the Secure Future Initiative uses AI-assisted continuous evaluation against its own live cloud services. No direct admin action is needed, but the post contains useful framing for organizations building or maturing their own cloud security validation programs.

